title.rendered: T20 World Cup 2022: Match 30, IND vs SA Match Prediction – Who will win?

content.rendered:
Who will win this Sunday?

Let us get ready to witness the epic battle of the World Cup T20. Match 30 of the World Cup T20 2022 is scheduled to take place between India and South Africa on Sunday 30 October 2022 at Perth Stadium in Perth. Safe, Accurate, and Reliable Match Predictions for the ICC T20 World Cup 2022 are released today.

India performed well at the 2022 ICC T20 World Cup, winning both matches. Let’s not forget that India is the only team in this tournament with two wins. After defeating Pakistan in a thrilling match, India beat the Netherlands by 56 runs in their next match.

South Africa also accomplished success so far in this tournament. They played and won two games, while the others ended with no results. They currently occupy second place in the points table. South Africa needs to win this game to improve its chances of qualifying for the semi-finals.

Weather forecast for today’s match

The Perth weather forecast calls for cloudy weather with a chance of rain on match day, but hopes for a full and uninterrupted match.

Pitch Reports and Conditions

The 30th match of the 2022 World Cup T20 will be played at Perth Stadium in Perth. In previous games here, the field at this location proved to be good for batting. The field is bouncy, and running early and mid-overs isn’t easy. Hopefully, the surface of this match will be slower and harder to hit. A score of 170 would be difficult to track.

Toss Predictions in Matches

Tosses play a key role in determining every match in the World Cup T20. In a big game like this, having a good board total is always a big advantage. According to the toss prediction, the team that wins the toss may choose to run first.

India is full of experienced young players in the t20 format. The team’s batting order is also strong, and with the T20 format’s famous hitters on the team’s roster, India has a good chance of winning today’s game. Below is the formula of who will win today’s cricket match prediction and who will win today’s cricket match.

Favorite Team Prediction

Overall, India is a stronger team compared to South Africa, at least in theory. According to cricket match predictions, India is the most popular team to win this match. Many factors make India the preferred team to win this game. India won both games played in this tournament. India’s main players are back in good shape.

South Africa has done well in this tournament too. This game is going to be very interesting, as both sides are strong.

India has a 52% chance of winning this match. South Africa has a 48% chance of winning this match

India vs. South Africa 1:1 match record

India played 23 games against South Africa with 9 wins and 13 wins compared to South Africa. This match between her two teams ended without a result.

Team Review – South Africa

South Africa won the previous game against Bangladesh by 104 runs after the first game was washed away by rain. They won the toss and decided to hit first. Their batting order in the previous game was just outstanding. They scored a total of 205 runs in 20 overs. Rilee Rossouw scored her first century at the 2022 ICC T20 Worlds Her Cup, the most successful with her team and her highest score. He scored a total of 109 runs in just 56 balls using seven Boundaries and his eight Giant Sixes. Q. de Kock also performed well, scoring 63 runs. He faced his 38 balls and smashed seven boundaries and three big sixes. Markram was only able to score 10 runs.

South African Bowling His unit had also performed well in the previous match, defending 206 runs of goal while he only lost 101 runs. They send the entire Bangladesh team back to the pavilion with 16.3 overs. Anrich Nortje was her team’s most successful and best wicket-taker as he took 4 wickets in 3.3 overs against just 10 runs. Tabraiz Shamsi was one bowler to destroy Bangladesh’s batting order. He took 3 wickets in 4 overs while being charged with 20 carries. Keshav Maharaj and Kagiso Rabada each picked a wicket. South Africa recently faced India in its series of three T20 games in India, but they face Australia and the situation is different for both teams.

Probable XI – South Africa

Quinton de Kock (wk), Temba Bavuma (c), Rilee Rossouw, Aiden Markram, David Miller, Tristan Stubbs, Wayne Parnell, Keshav Maharaj, Kagiso Rabada, Anrich Nortje, Tabraiz Shamsi.

Team Review – India

They won the draw and went first. After a slow start in the batting order, India picked up from 11th place and scored 179 points in 20 overs. Three batsmen India scored his 50th in the previous game. Virat Kohli scored 62 runs on 44 balls before scoring 3 borders and he was never left behind with the help of two big sixes, the most successful and best run by his scorer. did. Surya Kumar Yadav was the other hitter who put several runs on the board. He recorded 51 carries in just 25 balls. He broke 7 limits and 6 big limits during the inning. Rohit Sharma was another batsman who scored over 50 runs. He used his four Boundaries and his three Giant 6s to hit 53 carries on 39 balls.

The Indian bowling team was doing well in the previous round as well. They leaked 123 runs in 20 overs while defending 180 runs on goal. Almost all the team’s bowlers performed well in their previous matches. Bhuvneshwar Kumar was the team’s top bowler and he took two wickets in three overs for just nine runs. Axar Patel also performed well, with just 18 runs he took 4 overs and he took 2 wickets. Ravichandran Ashwin lost 21 runs but in four overs he took two wickets and he was already one bowler. Arshdeep Singh lost many runs although he picked up two wickets. He was charged with 37 runs in four overs. Mohammed Shami picked a wicket, but Hardik Pandya was the only bowler who failed to pick a wicket.

Probable XI –India

KL Rahul, Rohit Sharma (c), Virat Kohli, Surya Kumar Yadav, Hardik Pandya, Dinesh Karthik (wk), Axar Patel, Ravichandran Ashwin, Bhuvneshwar Kumar, Mohammed Shami, Arshdeep Singh.

Best players to watch in the match

Virat Kohli, KL Rahul, and Quinton de Kock are key players to watch in this match.
